01:01:23,880 --> 01:01:28,990
And that is Multitasking
in iOS 9.

1220
01:01:28,985 --> 01:01:34,825
[Applause]

1221
01:01:34,824 --> 01:01:38,064
So iOS 9 delivers this great
app switcher, and of course,

1222
01:01:38,061 --> 01:01:41,531
that's available
on iPhone as well.

1223
01:01:41,531 --> 01:01:44,631
On iPad, we have Slide
Over so you can bring apps

1224
01:01:44,634 --> 01:01:46,074
in from the side.

1225
01:01:46,069 --> 01:01:48,309
You can tap and enter split view

1226
01:01:48,305 --> 01:01:52,275
for simultaneous
live two apps up.

1227
01:01:52,275 --> 01:01:54,945
And of course, Picture
in Picture.

1228
01:01:54,945 --> 01:01:58,415
Now, we provide developer APIs
to let your apps work this way,

1229
01:01:58,415 --> 01:02:02,355
and the good news is that you've
already done most of that work

1230
01:02:02,352 --> 01:02:05,322
because if you've adopted
Auto Layout and size classes

1231
01:02:05,322 --> 01:02:09,262
to work great on the iPhone 6
and 6 Plus, well, that carries

1232
01:02:09,259 --> 01:02:13,599
over just like this onto iPad.

1233
01:02:13,597 --> 01:02:16,467
Twitter came in and was able
to do it just in minutes.

1234
01:02:16,466 --> 01:02:19,066
It was really incredible.

1235
01:02:19,069 --> 01:02:24,209
Now, Slide Over is available
for the iPad Air, Air 2, mini 2,

1236
01:02:24,207 --> 01:02:26,977
and mini 3, as is
Picture in Picture,

1237
01:02:26,977 --> 01:02:29,547
and our most powerful
split view is available

1238
01:02:29,546 --> 01:02:33,486
on our most powerful
iPad, the iPad Air 2.

1239
01:02:33,483 --> 01:02:35,053
That's Multitasking.

1240
01:02:35,051 --> 01:02:43,191
[Applause]

1241
01:02:43,193 --> 01:02:46,433
So we've seen some
great end-user features,

1242
01:02:46,429 --> 01:02:50,269
but of course, we've also
focused on the foundations.

1243
01:02:50,266 --> 01:02:56,206
In performance, as you saw
earlier in El Capitan with OS X,

1244
01:02:56,206 --> 01:02:59,206
we've taken the core frameworks
that we use for drawing

1245
01:02:59,209 --> 01:03:01,709
on the system, Core
Animation and Core Graphics,

1246
01:03:01,711 --> 01:03:02,911
and we put them on top of Metal.

1247
01:03:02,912 --> 01:03:04,912
We are seeing great
acceleration,

1248
01:03:04,914 --> 01:03:08,684
1.6 times improvements in
animations and scrolling,

1249
01:03:08,685 --> 01:03:11,625
and a 50 percent reduction
in CPU usage for drawing.

1250
01:03:11,621 --> 01:03:13,391
It's really great.

1251
01:03:13,390 --> 01:03:15,430
With battery life, we focused

1252
01:03:15,425 --> 01:03:19,165
on real-world use cases
and optimized them.

1253
01:03:19,162 --> 01:03:23,402
And we are seeing an addition
of one hour of typical use

1254
01:03:23,400 --> 01:03:26,100
on a full charge on iPhone.

1255
01:03:26,102 --> 01:03:30,512
[Applause]

1256
01:03:30,507 --> 01:03:32,777
Now, we know that for a lot
of you if you are running low

1257
01:03:32,776 --> 01:03:35,376
on power, you start searching
all over for switches

1258
01:03:35,378 --> 01:03:37,218
and turning off features
in the hope

1259
01:03:37,213 --> 01:03:40,353
of extending your battery
life a little bit further.

1260
01:03:40,350 --> 01:03:43,320
Well, now in iOS 9, we
give you a single switch

1261
01:03:43,319 --> 01:03:46,359
to enter what we call Low
Power mode, and it pulls levers

1262
01:03:46,356 --> 01:03:48,896
that you didn't even
know existed and is able

1263
01:03:48,892 --> 01:03:53,462
to extend battery life for
an additional three hours

1264
01:03:53,463 --> 01:03:55,963
of typical use on top
of that additional hour.

1265
01:03:55,965 --> 01:03:57,135
It's really great.

1266
01:03:57,133 --> 01:04:02,943
[Applause]

1267
01:04:02,939 --> 01:04:05,979
Now, with security, we want
to protect our users' data

1268
01:04:05,975 --> 01:04:07,615
on device and in the cloud,

1269
01:04:07,610 --> 01:04:10,250
and so we are bringing
two-factor authentication

1270
01:04:10,246 --> 01:04:15,216
and making it easy for everyone
to protect their data in iCloud.

1271
01:04:15,218 --> 01:04:20,428
And with Software Update, we
want everyone to get to iOS 9,

1272
01:04:20,423 --> 01:04:24,523
and so we've done major
enhancements to the architecture

1273
01:04:24,527 --> 01:04:26,797
for our over-the-air
updates, and we have been able

1274
01:04:26,796 --> 01:04:31,136
to reduce the amount of free
space you need to get to iOS 9

1275
01:04:31,134 --> 01:04:35,134
from the 4.6 gigs that
it took to get to iOS 8

1276
01:04:35,138 --> 01:04:37,808
down to just 1.3, so we
think everybody is going

1277
01:04:37,807 --> 01:04:39,177
to be getting to iOS 9.

1278
01:04:39,175 --> 01:04:45,345
[Applause]

1279
01:04:45,348 --> 01:04:48,348
So iOS 9, intelligence
throughout the system,

1280
01:04:48,351 --> 01:04:53,121
Apple Pay, enhancements to
really popular apps like Notes

1281
01:04:53,123 --> 01:04:58,533
and Maps, an all-new News app,
and incredible features now

1282
01:04:58,528 --> 01:05:01,928
for iPad with Multitasking
and QuickType, and of course,

1283
01:05:01,931 --> 01:05:04,301
enhancements to the foundations.

1284
01:05:04,300 --> 01:05:09,270
Now, iOS 9 is a great release
for our users, but once again,

1285
01:05:09,272 --> 01:05:13,512
it's a fantastic release
for all of you developers,

1286
01:05:13,510 --> 01:05:15,010
bringing a ton of new features.

1287
01:05:15,011 --> 01:05:16,551
You saw search extensibility.

1288
01:05:16,546 --> 01:05:19,486
We are adding UI
testing to Xcode.

1289
01:05:19,482 --> 01:05:20,582
[Cheers and applause] Yes!

1290
01:05:20,583 --> 01:05:24,683
We have a new technology
called App Thinning,

1291
01:05:24,687 --> 01:05:27,857
which optimizes your
downloads to exactly the subset

1292
01:05:27,857 --> 01:05:30,857
of resources needed for that
user's device, so you are able

1293
01:05:30,860 --> 01:05:33,230
to get -- take less
space on device.

1294
01:05:33,229 --> 01:05:34,729
It's really great.

1295
01:05:34,731 --> 01:05:37,871
Now, when it comes to gaming,
we've enhanced SpriteKit,

1296
01:05:37,867 --> 01:05:41,537
SceneKit, and Metal and
introduced three new frameworks,

1297
01:05:41,538 --> 01:05:44,038
GameplayKit to bring
artificial intelligence

1298
01:05:44,040 --> 01:05:48,380
with path avoid obstacle
avoidance and path finding;

1299
01:05:48,378 --> 01:05:50,618
Model I/O to provide
beautiful lighting

1300
01:05:50,613 --> 01:05:53,553
on your 3D models;
and ReplayKit.

1301
01:05:53,550 --> 01:05:55,690
It lets you enhance
your applications

1302
01:05:55,685 --> 01:06:00,195
to let users record their game
play as video and share it.

1303
01:06:00,190 --> 01:06:02,260
It's really great.

1304
01:06:02,258 --> 01:06:08,798
[Applause]

1305
01:06:08,798 --> 01:06:12,468
Now, HealthKit has been on
fire, so we've continued --

1306
01:06:12,468 --> 01:06:14,668
well, we added water,
actually, to HealthKit.

1307
01:06:14,671 --> 01:06:16,411
We are not trying
to put out the fire.

1308
01:06:16,406 --> 01:06:20,376
We are adding lots of additional
health metrics to be tracked,

1309
01:06:20,376 --> 01:06:23,746
for instance, hydration,
UV exposure,

1310
01:06:23,746 --> 01:06:25,486
and reproductive health.

1311
01:06:25,481 --> 01:06:29,251
Now, HomeKit has been taking off

1312
01:06:29,252 --> 01:06:31,592
with manufacturers
introducing HomeKit peripherals

1313
01:06:31,588 --> 01:06:36,758
to the market now in areas like
thermometers, locks, and lights.

1314
01:06:36,759 --> 01:06:39,229
And now in iOS 9, we
are adding support

1315
01:06:39,229 --> 01:06:42,229
for window shades,
sensors of all kinds.

1316
01:06:42,232 --> 01:06:46,002
For instance, carbon monoxide
sensors, motion sensors.

1317
01:06:46,002 --> 01:06:49,872
And we're adding support for
security systems as well.

1318
01:06:49,873 --> 01:06:52,443
Perhaps most importantly,
we are allowing you

1319
01:06:52,442 --> 01:06:57,252
to access your home remotely
and securely via iCloud.

1320
01:06:57,247 --> 01:07:00,047
So no matter where you
are, you can control all

1321
01:07:00,049 --> 01:07:02,319
of your HomeKit devices.

1322
01:07:02,318 --> 01:07:09,558
[Applause]

1323
01:07:09,559 --> 01:07:11,059
Next, CarPlay.

1324
01:07:11,060 --> 01:07:16,330
So CarPlay supports audio
apps and now, in iOS 9,

1325
01:07:16,332 --> 01:07:19,932
it also supports apps by the
automaker to control things

1326
01:07:19,936 --> 01:07:24,036
in your own car without
leaving the CarPlay experience.

1327
01:07:24,040 --> 01:07:26,540
And CarPlay is supporting
more kinds of screens,

1328
01:07:26,542 --> 01:07:28,842
wider aspect ratios, high DPI.

1329
01:07:28,845 --> 01:07:32,885
But most significantly
with CarPlay,

1330
01:07:32,882 --> 01:07:35,252
we are pulling the cord.

1331
01:07:35,251 --> 01:07:38,391
In future cars, you will
be able to get in your car

1332
01:07:38,388 --> 01:07:42,158
without taking your phone out of
your bag or out of your pocket

1333
01:07:42,158 --> 01:07:46,098
and start experiencing
CarPlay effortlessly.

1334
01:07:46,095 --> 01:07:48,365
It's going to be really great.

1335
01:07:48,364 --> 01:07:53,374
[Applause]

1336
01:07:53,369 --> 01:07:57,369
Finally, let's talk about Swift.

1337
01:07:57,373 --> 01:08:02,343
[Cheers and applause]

1338
01:08:02,345 --> 01:08:03,815
You all know that the growth

1339
01:08:03,813 --> 01:08:07,413
that Swift has been experiencing
is just unprecedented,

1340
01:08:07,417 --> 01:08:09,517
and we've all seen
it with the flood

1341
01:08:09,519 --> 01:08:12,789
of applications coming
in to the App Store.

1342
01:08:12,789 --> 01:08:18,099
Well, now we are stepping on
the gas this year with Swift 2.

1343
01:08:18,094 --> 01:08:21,434
Now, Swift was designed from
the beginning to be fast,

1344
01:08:21,431 --> 01:08:22,831
and we've continued to roll

1345
01:08:22,832 --> 01:08:26,772
out targeted optimizations all
year long, and now with Swift 2,

1346
01:08:26,769 --> 01:08:29,939
we have an all-new optimization
technology that's especially

1347
01:08:29,939 --> 01:08:33,409
great for complex applications
and object-oriented programming

1348
01:08:33,409 --> 01:08:36,409
that we call Whole
Module Optimization,

1349
01:08:36,412 --> 01:08:39,812
and the results are
really fantastic.

1350
01:08:39,816 --> 01:08:42,456
In addition, we are bringing
the language features

1351
01:08:42,452 --> 01:08:44,352
that you've asked for most,

1352
01:08:44,354 --> 01:08:46,524
an elegant new error
handling model,

1353
01:08:46,522 --> 01:08:48,322
the ability to see
your interfaces

1354
01:08:48,324 --> 01:08:51,894
as synthesized headers
in Xcode, and the feature

1355
01:08:51,894 --> 01:08:56,404
that Tim has been begging for
all year, protocol extensions.

1356
01:08:56,399 --> 01:08:59,099
You are all going to love it.

1357
01:08:59,102 --> 01:09:04,612
Now, we think Swift is the
next big programming language,

1358
01:09:04,607 --> 01:09:07,077
the one that we will
all be doing application

1359
01:09:07,076 --> 01:09:11,916
and systems programming
on for 20 years to come.

1360
01:09:11,914 --> 01:09:17,524
And we think Swift should be
everywhere and used by everyone,

1361
01:09:17,520 --> 01:09:20,560
and so we're going to be
doing something really big.

1362
01:09:20,556 --> 01:09:25,466
Today we are announcing that
Swift will be open source.

1363
01:09:25,461 --> 01:09:34,541
[Cheers and applause]

1364
01:09:48,885 --> 01:09:51,855
We will be rolling
out the compiler

1365
01:09:51,854 --> 01:09:56,964
and the standard libraries
for iOS, OS X, and Linux.

1366
01:09:56,959 --> 01:10:02,599
And it will all be out there
by the end of the year.

1367
01:10:02,598 --> 01:10:04,538
So that's Swift,
and that is iOS 9.

1368
01:10:04,534 --> 01:10:07,774
We are doing a developer
beta -- you guessed it --

1369
01:10:07,770 --> 01:10:10,940
today, and for the first
time for a major iOS release,

1370
01:10:10,940 --> 01:10:14,810
a public beta, so sign
up now at beta.apple.com,

1371
01:10:14,811 --> 01:10:17,151
and you can get the beta
when it comes out in July.

1372
01:10:17,146 --> 01:10:19,086
And of course, we
will be rolling it

1373
01:10:19,082 --> 01:10:21,182
out as a free upgrade
in the fall.

1374
01:10:21,184 --> 01:10:25,984
And iOS 9 will support
all of the devices

1375
01:10:25,988 --> 01:10:27,688
that were supported by iOS 8.

1376
01:10:27,690 --> 01:10:29,090
We are not dropping
any this year

1377
01:10:29,092 --> 01:10:32,032
because we want everyone
to get iOS 9.

1378
01:10:32,028 --> 01:10:33,928
[Applause]

1379
01:10:33,930 --> 01:10:34,830
That's iOS 9.

1380
01:10:34,831 --> 01:10:36,631
I really appreciate your time.

1381
01:10:36,632 --> 01:10:37,472
Have a fantastic conference.

1382
01:10:37,467 --> 01:10:38,537
Thank you.

1383
01:10:38,534 --> 01:10:45,944
